# Zero-Cost Constraint

This project is a zero-cost Perplexity-style engine. No paid services.

## Allowed (free)

- **Web search**: SearxNG (self-hosted in the container). Only SearxNG.
- **Embeddings**: Gemini `gemini-embedding-001` via Google AI Studio free
  tier (OpenAI-compatible endpoint).
- **Chat / research / writer LLM**: GLM models via z.ai
  (`https://api.z.ai/api/coding/paas/v4`) using the user's Coding Plan key.
- **Scraping**: Playwright + `@mozilla/readability` (in-process).

## Never wire these

- Tavily, Exa, SerpAPI, Brave Search **API** (paid) — note: SearxNG's
  built-in `brave` scraper engine is fine, that's not the paid API.
- Cohere Rerank or any paid reranker.
- OpenAI API for chat or embeddings.
- Any other paid LLM/search/embedding/rerank service.

## If a feature needs a paid service

Stop. Flag it to the user explicitly. Propose a free alternative (a
code-only algorithmic improvement, a free-tier service, or a local model).
Do not silently add a paid dependency.

## Keys

API keys (z.ai, Gemini) live in `config.json` inside the `vane-data`
volume — never in source files, env files committed to git, or the
Dockerfile. See the `vane-ops` skill for the volume-edit workflow.
